                                    SC voted one by one on separate
                                    ballots through list of ten candidates. Results announced at end
                                    as follows: 


                                            Amerasinghe
                                            (4–6–5); Djermakoye (5–8–2);


                                            Herrera (7–6–2);
                                                Jakobson (9–5
                                            (including one veto)–1);


                                            Jarring (7–4–4);
                                                Ortiz de
                                                Rozas (10–3 (one veto)–2);


                                            Rahnema (3–8–4);
                                                Ramphal
                                            (3–7–5);

Valdes (7–5–3); Waldheim (11–2 (one veto)–2).
